adjective.description: Zoology. Of or designating certain vestigial, embryonic toothlike structures occurring in the jaws of marsupials and some other mammals, regarded as the remnants of two successive primitive dentitions that formed prior to the development of the milk teeth.
Designating a foodstuff or feed that is given to a newborn infant before the mother has begun to breastfeed.

origin: Late 19th century; earliest use found in Science. From pre- + lacteal.
